OL,7,FTheir insistence that they can cope is
OL,8,Foften taken at face value without
OL,9,Fconsidering their past history and
OL,10,Frelatives' concerns. This means that -
OL,11,Fas in Christopher Laskaris' case -
OL,12,Fthey are left without the support they
OL,13,Fneed.
OL,15,F"One of the problems in Christopher's
OL,16,Fcase was that when mental capacity
OL,17,Fassessments should have been carried
OL,18,Fout, they weren't, because they were
OL,19,Fjust assuming that he had capacity,"
OL,20,Fhis mother Fiona previously told ITV
OL,21,FNews.
